When they arrived in Plett on Friday, other people were staying at the accommodation they paid for. CAPE TOWN - Plett Rage organisers say at least 15 matriculants have reported they have been defrauded in an apparent accommodation scam.Eyewitness News understands some matriculants were scammed while booking packages online.When they arrived in Plett on Friday, other people were staying at the accommodation they paid for.Organiser Ronen Klugman said: We ve spoken to one of our service providers and we re going to be putting up free tents for the students and they can stay at the Rage camp site. This way they will have an option if they want to and they ve got a bed to sleep in. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)